race.comment: DEMARCAY (3) loves this track and trip with two wins and two placings from six attempts and rarely puts in a poor one. Finds a suitable race here and should be right there when the whips are cracking. LOVEY DOVEY (7) got the job done over this course and distance last time out and must be respected out of the champion Waller yard. Include in calculations. STYNSY (8) has been well in the betting in all three runs this campaign and where there's smoke there's fire. Don't dismiss lightly. ABOVEFORTY (6) has a handy record over this staying trip with two wins and a second from just three outings. Makes some appeal.
